2026-07-23 15:34:18.439 | INFO     | metagpt.roles.di.role_zero:_act:292 - Commands: 
[{'command_name': 'RoleZero.reply_to_human', 'args': {'content': 'Fix applied successfully for crun-129 OCI runtime bug.\n\n**Root Cause**: When a prestart hook exits non-zero (e.g., `/bin/false`), the parent process calls `cleanup_watch()` without first sending a sync message to the child process. The child is blocked waiting for this sync message on the sync socket. Both processes end up waiting on each other - a classic deadlock.\n\n**Sync Protocol**:\n1. Parent sends sync → Child receives sync, continues setup\n2. Child sends sync → Parent receives sync\n3. Parent starts prestart hooks → If hook fails, deadlock occurs\n\n**Fix**: Send `sync_socket_send_sync(sync_socket, false, err)` before every `cleanup_watch()` call in `container_run_internal()` to unblock the child process. This allows the child to receive the sync, realize the parent had an error, and exit cleanly.\n\n**Changed file**: `src/libcrun/container.c`\n\n**Test result**: The reproduction case completed without hanging, exiting promptly with a hook failure error, matching the expected differential behavior.'}}]
